                        <h3>Description</h3>
                        <p>This is a sketch I made using the <a href="https://p5js.org/" target="_empty">p5.js</a> library. A neat and simple way to visualize the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A*_search_algorithm" target="_empty">A*</a>, the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Depth-first_search" target="_empty">Depth-First Search</a> and the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breadth-first_search" target="_empty">Breadth-First Search</a> algorithms.</p>
                        <p>When using the A* algorithm, you can choose to use the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euclidean_distance">Euclidean</a> or the <a href="https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Manhattan_distance">Manhattan</a> heuristic. You can set/remove obstacles just by clicking on the grid, and by double clicking you can set/remove the goal (red) and starting (green) cells.</p>
                        <p>You can take a look at the code <a href="/projects/astar/code">here</a> and if you want to have a bigger version of it, you can get it <a href="/projects/astar/app">here</a>.</p>
